%% Kueue Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(in-process)
    participant WLCtrl as Workload Controller<br/>(in-process)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Job Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create job/pytorchjob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-*<br/>443->9443/TCP TLS<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Suspend job, inject<br/>queue-name label
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated job (suspended=true)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-*<br/>443->9443/TCP TLS<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response

    Note over Webhook,Scheduler: Workload created for suspended job

    K8sAPI-->>WLCtrl: Watch event: new Workload CR
    WLCtrl->>WLCtrl: Track pod readiness<br/>and admission state

    Note over Scheduler,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Workload Scheduling Cycle

    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate pending workloads<br/>against ClusterQueue quota
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: PATCH Workload (admit)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>WLCtrl: Watch event: Workload admitted
    WLCtrl->>K8sAPI: PATCH Job (unsuspend)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job pods start running

    Note over Prometheus,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Webhook: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA token)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Auth validated
    Webhook-->>Prometheus: Metrics response (kueue_*)
